HEADWORD: Cerebrifugal
<hw>Cer`e*brif"u*gal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cerebrum</ets> + L. <ets>fugere</ets> to flee.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Applied to those nerve fibers which go from
the brain to the spinal cord, and so transfer cerebral impulses
(centrifugal impressions) outwards.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerebrin</ent>⟦br⟧
